Class Character

  • java.lang.Object
    • Character
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefensiveCharacter, OffensiveCharacter, Potions
    public abstract class Character
extends Object
    This class stores information about a character that exists on the simulation. It contains information such as its name, its energy, offensive and defensive points, or the wand it wields.
    Version:
    5/12/2019
    Author:
    Jorge Cancho Casado, Rubén Costa Barriga and Arturo Mejías Velasco

      • fight

        public void fight​(Character opponent)
        Simulates a fight between two characters. This method checks attacker's attack points and defender's resistance points. If attacker's attack points are greater than defender's defensive points, defender's energy will decrease.
        Parameters:
        opponent - The character it fights against.
